{"heading":[["1–4","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/76.1-4"],", The Lord is God; ",["5–10","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/76.5-10"],", The mysteries of the kingdom will be revealed to all the faithful; ",["11–17","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/76.11-17"],", All will come forth in the resurrection of the just or the unjust; ",["18–24","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/76.18-24"],", The inhabitants of many worlds are begotten sons and ",137,"daughters unto God through the Atonement of Jesus Christ; ",["25–29","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/76.25-29"],", An angel of God fell and became the devil; ",["30–49","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/76.30-49"],", Sons of perdition suffer eternal damnation; all others gain some degree of salvation; ",["50–70","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/76.50-70"],", The glory and reward of exalted beings in the celestial kingdom is described; ",["71–80","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/76.71-80"],", Those who will inherit the terrestrial kingdom are described; ",["81–113","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/76.81-113"],", The status of those in the telestial, terrestrial, and celestial glories is explained; ",["114–19","scripture-ref","dc-testament/dc/76.114-119"],", The faithful may see and understand the mysteries of God’s kingdom by the power of the Holy Spirit."],"number":76,"verseCount":119,"verses":[[1,[["Hear",["study-note-ref","a",[["Isa. 1:2","ot/isa/1.2"],"."]]],", O ye heavens, and give ear, O earth, and rejoice ye inhabitants thereof, for the Lord is ",["God",["study-note-ref","b",[["Josh. 22:34","ot/josh/22.34"],"; ",["Jer. 10:10","ot/jer/10.10"],"."]]],", and beside him there is ",["no",["study-note-ref","c",[["Ex. 8:10 (8–10)","ot/ex/8.10"],"; ",["1 Kgs. 8:60","ot/1-kgs/8.60"],"; ",["Isa. 43:11","ot/isa/43.11"],"; ",["Hosea 13:4","ot/hosea/13.4"],"."]]]," ",["Savior",["study-note-ref","d",[["TG Jesus Christ, Savior","tg/jesus-christ-savior"],"."]]],"."]],[2,[["Great",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 15:11","ot/ex/15.11"],". ",[